- Nothing says

00:10.542 --> 00:12.500
"First day of the new quarter"

00:12.542 --> 00:14.583
like a freshly-laminated

00:12.542 --> 00:14.583
schedule.

00:14.625 --> 00:16.500
- Who needs laminating

00:14.625 --> 00:16.500
when you got a hand?

00:16.542 --> 00:19.208
This period, I have... mystery.

00:19.875 --> 00:21.458
- You mean "History."

00:19.875 --> 00:21.458
- No.

00:21.500 --> 00:22.917
I have no idea what this says.

00:24.041 --> 00:26.709
- Well, the three of us

00:24.041 --> 00:26.709
have art class.

00:27.000 --> 00:28.834
Finally, a reason

00:27.000 --> 00:28.834
to wear this beret.

00:29.166 --> 00:30.583
- Plus, art's an easy A.

00:30.792 --> 00:32.667
But then, for me,

00:30.792 --> 00:32.667
aren't they all?

00:33.917 --> 00:36.125
- Wow, new quarter,

00:33.917 --> 00:36.125
same old Ricky,

00:36.166 --> 00:37.291
already bragging

00:36.166 --> 00:37.291
about his grades.

00:37.333 --> 00:39.500
- If it's true,

00:37.333 --> 00:39.500
it's not bragging.

00:39.542 --> 00:41.083
It's just talking.

00:41.125 --> 00:43.333
- Well, it sounds to me

00:41.125 --> 00:43.333
like trash talking.

00:43.375 --> 00:45.375
- No, this is trash talking:

00:45.417 --> 00:47.166
I'm gonna get a better grade

00:45.417 --> 00:47.166
than you in art class

00:47.208 --> 00:49.166
and then,

00:47.208 --> 00:49.166
I'm gonna brag about it.

00:50.709 --> 00:53.500
- Hey, are you guys coming to

00:50.709 --> 00:53.500
the Student Events Club after

00:50.709 --> 00:53.500
school?

00:53.542 --> 00:55.417
We really need some ideas

00:53.542 --> 00:55.417
for the spring festival.

00:55.458 --> 00:57.500
- Definitely.

00:55.458 --> 00:57.500
- I'll bring chips.

00:57.542 --> 00:58.959
- I can bring some dip.

00:59.000 --> 01:01.417
- Why am I just now

00:59.000 --> 01:01.417
hearing about this club?

01:01.458 --> 01:02.709
Where do I sign up?

01:02.750 --> 01:04.083
- Dicky, that club's all about

01:04.125 --> 01:06.208
organizing events

01:04.125 --> 01:06.208
and coming up with ideas.

01:06.250 --> 01:09.709
- Uh, yeah,

01:06.250 --> 01:09.709
with chips and girls.

01:09.750 --> 01:11.000
[bell rings]

01:11.041 --> 01:14.041
[rock music]

01:14.083 --> 01:15.750
- You know, Ricky, I am

01:14.083 --> 01:15.750
pretty good at art.

01:15.792 --> 01:18.208
I wouldn't be so sure

01:15.792 --> 01:18.208
you're going to be better at it

01:15.792 --> 01:18.208
than me.

01:18.250 --> 01:19.750
- Please, I've been coloring

01:18.250 --> 01:19.750
inside the lines

01:19.792 --> 01:21.333
since I was three.

01:21.375 --> 01:24.166
Pretty sure I got this.

01:24.208 --> 01:26.250
- Pablo Picasso once said that

01:26.291 --> 01:28.750
"Art is a lie...

01:28.792 --> 01:32.250
that tells the truth."

01:32.291 --> 01:35.333
- What does that even mean?

01:32.291 --> 01:35.333
- Exactly!

01:37.625 --> 01:40.166
I believe we all

01:40.208 --> 01:42.959
have an artist

01:40.208 --> 01:42.959
who lives inside of us,

01:43.000 --> 01:44.709
screaming to get out.

01:44.750 --> 01:47.917
[screams]

01:49.166 --> 01:51.125
So today, I want you

01:51.166 --> 01:54.500
to create a piece

01:51.166 --> 01:54.500
that expresses you.

01:54.542 --> 01:56.125
Your-- your hopes,

01:56.166 --> 01:57.709
your dreams,

01:57.750 --> 01:58.917
your truth.

01:58.959 --> 02:00.750
- Oh, can I paint

01:58.959 --> 02:00.750
a self-portrait?

02:00.792 --> 02:02.291
- Any subject.

02:02.333 --> 02:04.208
- Ooh, uh, can I make

02:02.333 --> 02:04.208
something out of food?

02:04.250 --> 02:06.250
- Any medium.

02:04.250 --> 02:06.250
- [gasps] Sweet!

02:06.291 --> 02:08.333
Or salty.

02:06.291 --> 02:08.333
Haven't decided yet.

02:09.917 --> 02:11.583
- Um, what about a paper?

02:11.792 --> 02:12.917
- Yes, you can use paper.

02:12.959 --> 02:15.417
- Uh, no.

02:12.959 --> 02:15.417
Can I write a paper?

02:15.458 --> 02:16.792
- Oh. [laughs]

02:16.834 --> 02:18.208
This assignment isn't about

02:18.250 --> 02:20.250
writing papers, right?

02:20.291 --> 02:24.208
It's about

02:20.291 --> 02:24.208
expressing our creativity.

02:24.250 --> 02:26.417
- So, what are the guidelines?

02:24.250 --> 02:26.417
- There are no guidelines.

02:26.458 --> 02:27.667
- Then can I write a paper?

02:27.709 --> 02:30.166
- There is one guideline.

02:27.709 --> 02:30.166
No papers.

02:30.208 --> 02:33.750
- So, what should I make?

02:30.208 --> 02:33.750
- Anything you like.

02:33.792 --> 02:36.166
Just express yourself!

02:36.208 --> 02:37.208
- Well, I'd like to express

02:37.250 --> 02:39.750
how much I'd like

02:37.250 --> 02:39.750
some guidelines.

02:39.792 --> 02:42.000
How else will I know

02:39.792 --> 02:42.000
how to get an A?

02:42.041 --> 02:43.250
- Oh, we don't have grades

02:42.041 --> 02:43.250
in here.

02:43.291 --> 02:44.583
[both gasp]

02:44.625 --> 02:46.291
All right, class.

02:46.333 --> 02:47.875
On your marks...

02:47.917 --> 02:49.750
get set...

02:49.792 --> 02:51.125
create!

02:52.917 --> 02:55.667
- [breathing heavily]

02:55.709 --> 02:57.583
- I hear something.

02:57.625 --> 02:58.959
Oh.

02:59.000 --> 03:00.166
I think it's the little artist

03:00.208 --> 03:03.750
inside of you crying.

